                                                           /*    QUICK SORT    */
1.Invented in the year 1959.
2.Inventor --> Richard Hoare (Turing award in 1980)
3.One of the top 10 algorithsm invented.
4.Sub rotiune --> Partitioning.
5.Pivot element is the word used frequently in quick sort.
PARTITIONING:
1. Take a pivot element(generally either the last or first element)
2. Re-Arrange the array in such a way 
   a. every value present on the left part of pivot is smaller or equals to the pivot.
   b. every value presesnt on the right part of the pivot is larger or equals the pivot

1.Naive Partitioning scheme.
2.Lomuto Partitioning scheme.
3.Hoare's ppartitionning scheme.
